, 
<collectingCountry id="F36176127D6FD110FF40572EFEF90660" box="[246,315,1092,1114]" name="Brazil" pageId="119" pageNumber="119">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(fig. 40).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C65097D6FD110FF2A570AFDFB06EA" pageId="119" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC936827D6FD110FF2A570AFDFB06EA" blockId="119.[128,654,213,1232]" pageId="119" pageNumber="119">
REMARKS: The 
<typeStatus id="54CD88207D6FD110FEEF5708FE000642" box="[345,450,1122,1144]" pageId="119" pageNumber="119">lectotype</typeStatus>
is reddish brown and may be slightly teneral; the 
<typeStatus id="54CD88207D6FD110FE465715FD4C06AF" box="[496,654,1151,1173]" pageId="119" pageNumber="119">paralectotype</typeStatus>
is dark reddish brown. Only the 
<typeStatus id="54CD88207D6FD110FD9357F6FD4C0688" box="[549,654,1180,1202]" pageId="119" pageNumber="119">lectotype</typeStatus>
was dissected for genitalic characters.
</paragraph>
